<H3> <TI>   Talk Claims U.S. Forces in Japan Have Aggressive Aim </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Talk Claims U.S. Forces in Japan Have Aggressive Aim </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   SK1705040894 Pyongyang Korean Central Broadcasting Network 
in Korean 1620 GMT 15 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> SK1705040894 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang Korean Central Broadcasting Network 
in Korean 1620 GMT 15 May 94 </F>

<F P=105> Korean </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Unattributed talk: "The Aggressor Forces Aimed at Asian </F>
Countries"] 
  [Text] While the United States is intensifying its 
strong-arm politics against our Republic under the pretext of 
the nuclear issue, the U.S. Forces in Japan are making dangerous 
moves. The U.S. Forces' military exercises are frequently 
conducted in various places in Japan, and the aircraft carriers 
and nuclear submarines are frequently calling at Japanese ports. 
This shows that the U.S. bellicose circles continue to pursue 
their Korean and Asian policy from a force-oriented position 
[himui ipchangeso]. 
  It is the invariable U.S. policy to maintain and intensify 
the domination over the Asia-Pacific region. This U.S. policy 
is becoming more conspicuous today when the power balance is 
broken in the international arena. The United States is 
particularly nervous about the Western powers taking increasing 
interest in this region in recent years with the economic 
development of the countries of the Asia-Pacific region and with 
the strategic importance and significance of this region brought 
to the fore. This is leading the United States to head in the 
direction of further strengthening its influence and power 
sphere over the Asia-Pacific region. Here the U.S. ruling 
circles give great significance to the force-oriented policy 
[himui chongchaek]. A typical example of this is the present 
U.S. scheme to continuously maintain and strengthen the U.S. 
Forces and their bases in Japan under the pretext of our nuclear 
issue. 
  The U.S. and Japanese reactionaries are claiming that the 
maintenance and strengthening of the U.S. Forces in Japan is 
aimed at strengthening the Japan-U.S. security. But this is a 
lie, and a deception and mockery at the peace-loving people of 
Asia and the world. 
  It is not hard to know this from the composition and the 
particulars of the U.S. Armed Forces in Japan. The U.S. Armed 
Forces in Japan are the mobile strike forces of an offensive 
type composed of the Army, Navy, and Air Force. They have all 
the arms and equipment--from tactical to strategic 
weapons--enabling them to carry out operations in any region of 
Asia, and their function is to carry out the role of a shock 
brigade for the aggressive U.S. Asian strategy. 
  The U.S. Forces and their bases in Japan participate, 
without 
exception, in the war exercises conducted in the Asia-Pacific 
region, and are used as supply and launching bases for war 
exercises. Here they are strengthening the operational and 
commanding system among the U.S., Japanese, and South Korean 
forces and accelerating the preparations for overseas 
aggression. This shows that the U.S. Forces in Japan are not 
for the Japan-U.S. security but they are aggressor forces aimed 
at the Asia-Pacific region using Japan and South Korea as a 
stepping stone. 
  The U.S. Armed Forces in Japan are the nuclear forces aimed 
at maintaining nuclear superiority in the Asia-Pacific region 
and attacking other countries. Not to be overlooked is the fact 
that the operational focus of the U.S. Armed Forces in Japan is 
directed at our country. The U.S. imperialists, who overturned 
[twijibo opun] the DPRK-U.S. talks, are busily moving the U.S. 
Armed Forces in Japan, babbling about coping with our nuclear 
development. The U.S. Armed Forces in Japan aimed at our 
country are prepared to be put into war at any time. 
  The U.S. ruling circles are advertising, brazen-facedly, 
that 
the U.S. Forces in Japan are a so-called war-deterrent. This is 
nothing but a sophistry. The U.S. Forces and their bases in 
Japan are the source of misfortune that threatens the 
sovereignty, independence, peace, and security of our country 
and other countries in Asia. 
  The United States should immediately withdraw its Armed 
Forces in conformity with today's environment in which the Cold 
War ended, and clearly know that the force-oriented policy is 
far from an omnipotent prescription. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

