against mankind and peace as the greatest charity, will never 
tolerate their nuclear arms development for plunging the nation 
into a nuclear disaster," he declared. 
  "The KBF Central Committee calls on the Korean Buddhists in 
the South and overseas to actively join in the struggle for 
checking the South Korean puppets' nuclear arms development and 
getting the U.S. troops and nuclear weapons withdrawn from South 
Korea, thus fully discharging the mission and duty of Buddhists, 
who consider avoiding sin of killing any living creature most 
important in the Buddhist commandments. [no closing quotation 
mark as received] 

