<H3> <TI>   Japan's `Suppression' of Chongnyon Decried </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Japan's `Suppression' of Chongnyon Decried </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   SK1605115194 Pyongyang KCNA in English 1034 GMT 16 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK1605115194 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Tokyo, May 13 (KNS-KCNA) -- A forum on human rights 
of Koreans in Japan sent a message on May 12 to the prime 
minister, the chairman of the state security committee, the 
director of the police agency and the chief of the Osaka 
prefectural police headquarters of Japan protesting the 
unprecedented outrages of the Japanese police authorities 
against the Osaka prefectural headquarters of the General 
Association of Korean Residents in Japan (Chongnyon) and its 
branches. 
  The forum in the message denounced the forcible search by 
the 
Osaka prefectural police on the Osaka prefectural headquarters 
of Chongnyon and its branches as a wanton encroachment on the 
freedom and human rights of Koreans in Japan. 
  The message strongly demanded an immediate stop to the 
political suppression, watch and violation of human rights of 
the Chongnyon organisations and Koreans in Japan. 

</TEXT>

