<F P=100> North Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   Chongnyon Proposes Unity to Mindan Compatriots </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Chongnyon Proposes Unity to Mindan Compatriots </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   SK1505091294 Pyongyang KCNA in English 0836 GMT 15 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK1505091294 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, May 15 (KCNA) -- The Central Standing 
Committee of the General Association of Korean Residents in 
Japan (Chongnyon) sent an appeal to the compatriots affiliated 
with the "ROK Residents Association in Japan" (Mindan) on May 
12, urging it to promote national unity for defense of national 
dignity and vital rights of the Koreans in Japan. 
  Noting that the persecution and suppression of Koreans in 
Japan and Chongnyon organisations by the Japanese reactionaries 
today are by no means confined to Chongnyon, the appeal says: 
  Militarism does not distinguish between Chongnyon and 
"Mindan" and between the North and the South of Korea. We 
cannot and must not allow the past history of humiliation and 
shame to be repeated, falling a prey to the malicious scheme of 
the Japanese militarist forces to sow discord within our nation. 
  There is only one way for the Korean nationals in Japan to 
survive, defending national dignity and rights--a close unity of 
the nation. 
  We are sending this appeal to you, loudly asserting that it 
is high time all the Koreans in Japan closely united, sharply 
watching the heinous militarist ambition of the Japanese 
reactionary forces against Korea and their possible nation 
alienating maneuvers. 
  Let us all unite as fellow countrymen, irrespective of isms 
and views and affiliation, defend the dignity of the nation and 
the vital rights of the compatriots in Japan and guarantee the 
future of our dear younger generations. 
  Let us achieve national reunification in the 1990s without 
fail by uniting as fellow countrymen of the same ancestry, 
priding ourselves on our long history spanning 50 centuries. 

</TEXT>

