<H3> <TI>   `National Persecution' by Japanese Denounced </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    `National Persecution' by Japanese Denounced </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   SK1605104794 Pyongyang KCNA in English 1008 GMT 16 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK1605104794 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Tokyo, May 14 (KNS-KCNA) -- A Kinki District meeting 
of Koreans in Japan was held in Osaka on May 13 to denounce the 
suppression of the Osaka organisation of the General Association 
of Korean Residents in Japan (Chongnyon) and national 
persecution by the Japanese authorities. 
  Addressing the meeting, vice chairman of Chongnyon O 
Hyong-chin said that the recent outrage is part of the anti-DPRK 
campaign of the U.S., Japanese and South Korean reactionaries 
over the fictitious "nuclear suspicion" against the North and an 
attempt to destroy the patriotic activities of Chongnyon. 
  "It cannot be overlooked that the Japanese reactionaries, 
far 
from repenting of their past Asian aggression, are trying to 
turn Japan back to the road of militarism and purposefully 
inciting among the Japanese people national chauvinism and ill 
feelings against the Koreans in Japan," he said. 
  He strongly demanded that the Japanese police immediately 
stop unreasonable political suppression of Chongnyon and 
apologize for it. 
  At the meeting Japanese guests made speeches of solidarity 
and participants delivered indignation speeches. 
  A letter of protest was adopted and a protest group was 
formed to hand it to the Osaka prefectural police headquarters 
and the Higashi police station. 
  After the meeting the participants staged a powerful street 
demonstration. 

</TEXT>

