<H3> <TI>   Radio Society Urges Improved Ties With Japan </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Radio Society Urges Improved Ties With Japan </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   SK1305225894 Pyongyang KCNA in English 1502 GMT 13 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK1305225894 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, May 13 (KCNA) -- A statement demanding 
early normalization of Japan-DPRK diplomatic relations was 
adopted at an inaugural meeting of the National Interchange 
Society of Listeners to Radio Pyongyang, which was held in Osaka 
on April 17. 
  The statement demanded that the Japanese Government rectify 
the external policy, with which it, following the U.S. Korea 
policy, has been hostile to the DPRK and joined in freezing the 
division of the Korean peninsula. 
  For Japan to normalize diplomatic relations with the DPRK is 
to put an end to the past hostile relations and make a true 
international contribution, the statement said, and stressed: 
  The Japanese Government should normalize Japan-Korea 
diplomatic relations, not clamouring for "sanctions" against the 
DPRK. 
  The statement urged the Japanese Government to respect the 
spirit of the joint declaration published by the Liberal 
Democratic Party and Social Democratic Party of Japan and the 
Workers' Party of Korea on September 28, 1990, and propel 
negotiations for the normalization of Japan-Korea diplomatic 
relations in this spirit. 
  "The members of the National Interchange Society of 
Listeners 
to Radio Pyongyang will conduct a more energetic movement to 
realize negotiations for the normalization of Japan-Korea 
diplomatic relations," it declared. 

</TEXT>

