<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, May 16 (KCNA) -- Friendship organisations 
of Japan called for a detente on the Korean peninsula. 
  The Kochi prefectural council for the promotion of 
Japan-Korea friendship in a statement April 11 said tensions 
will increase and the danger of war will not disappear in the 
world as long as the United States continues to seek "domination 
of the world by strength". It demanded an immediate halt to the 
clamor for "sanctions" against the Democratic People's Republic 
of Korea. 
  The statement urged that the United States should 
discontinue 
