its forces from South Korea and sign a peace agreement with the 
DPRK through talks with it. 
  Speaking at the sixth Kennan, Ibaraki Prefecture, 
Japan-Korea 
friendship district meeting held on April 24, the chairman of 
the Kennan district liaison council for Japan-Korea solidarity, 
Tamaru Kawaguchi, said the nuclear issue on the Korean peninsula 
must be settled through DPRK-U.S. talks. 
  A letter of request to the Japanese Government was adopted 
at 
the meeting. 

</TEXT>

