<F P=100> North Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   Lao Delegation Departs Pyongyang </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Lao Delegation Departs Pyongyang </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   SK1405112994 Pyongyang KCNA in English 1053 GMT 14 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK1405112994 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, May 14 (KCNA) -- A high-level delegation 
of the Ministry of National Defence of Laos headed by Sai-ngason 
Choummali, Politburo member of the C.C. [Central Committee], the 
Lao People's Revolutionary Party and minister of national 
defence, left Pyongyang today, wrapping up its six-day visit to 
Korea. 
  It was seen off at the airport by Politburo member of the 
C.C., the Workers' Party of Korea and Chief of the General Staff 
of the Korean People's Army [KPA] Choe Kwang, Vice-Marshal Kim 
Kwang-chin, and generals and officers of the KPA. 
  A farewell function for the delegation took place at the 
airport. 
  While staying in Korea, the delegation paid visits to 
Mangyongdae, the Tower of Chuche Idea, the Grand People's Study 
House, KPA units, the victorious fatherland liberation war 
museum and other places. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

