<F P=100> North Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   Special Envoy's Visit to South Africa Detailed </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Special Envoy's Visit to South Africa Detailed </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   SK1605034494 </F>
<F P=103> SK1605034494 </F>
<F P=104></F>



<TEXT>
BFN 

    [Editorial Report] The following is a compilation of 
reports by Pyongyang Korean Central Broadcasting Network in 
Korean between 12 and 14 May summing up the visit of Yang 
Hyong-sop, chairman of DPRK Supreme People's Assembly, to South 
Africa to attend the presidential inauguration ceremony. 
  At 1300 GMT on 12 May, the radio reports that Yang Hyong-sop 
"on 9 and 10 May met with South African President Nelson 
Mandela; its former President De Klerk; Fidel Castro, president 
of the Council of Ministers of the Republic of Cuba; Senegalese 
President Abdou Diouf; Angolan President Jose Eduardo dos 
Santos; Ugandan President Yoweri Kaguta Museveni; Botswana 
President Ketumile Masire; Palestinian President Yasir 'Arafat; 
Zimbabwean President Robert Mugabe; Ethiopian interim government 
President Meles Zenawi; Tanzanian President Ali Hassyan Mwinyi; 
Seychelles President France Albert Rene; Mozambican President 
Joaquim Alberto Chissano; Namibian President Sam Nujoma; 
Gabonese President El Hadj Omar Bongo; Pakistani Premier Benazir 
Bhutto; and UN Secretary General Butrus Butrus-Ghali." 
  Then the radio reports that Yang Hyong-sop met with "the 
vice 
presidents and foreign ministers of various countries, including 
the United States, Afghanistan, Bolivia, Indonesia, and 
Suriname." 
  At 1300 GMT on 14 May, the radio reports on the departure of 
Yang Hyong-sop from Johannesburg on 12 May. It says he was seen 
off at the airport by members of the presidential inauguration 
ceremony organizing committee. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

