<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, May 14 (KCNA) -- The government 
delegation of the Republic of Zimbabwe led by Minister of Home 
Affairs Dumiso Dabengwa left here today after a five-day visit 
to Korea. 
  During its stay the delegation visited Mangyongdae, and saw 
the Tower of the Chuche Idea, the Arch of Triumph, the West Sea 
barrage, the victorious fatherland liberation war museum, the 
Kang Kon Military Academy and other places. 

</TEXT>

