<F P=100> North Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   Messages, Letters to Kim Il-song Adopted Abroad </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Messages, Letters to Kim Il-song Adopted Abroad </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   SK1505085694 Pyongyang KCNA in English 0816 GMT 15 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK1505085694 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, May 15 (KCNA) -- The great leader 
President Kim Il-song received congratulatory messages from the 
participants in celebration meetings which were held in Tulubolo 
and Western Shoa region, Ethiopia, in Damascus, Syria and by the 
Chittagong Branch of the Bangladesh-Korea Friendship 
Association, on his birthday. 
  The messages say President Kim Il-song enjoys deep respect 
from the world's peaceloving and democratic forces for having 
devoted his all to the happiness of the people and victory of 
the Korean revolution. 
  Noting that the chuche idea founded by President Kim Il-song 
is the one and only just ideological weapon for the working 
peoples of the world to free themselves from exploitation and 
oppression by imperialism, they express the resolution to deepen 
the study of it. 
  They also express firm solidarity with the Korean people in 
the struggle for the peaceful reunification of the country and 
building of socialism, saying "10-point programme of the great 
unity of the whole nation for the reunification of the country" 
worked out by President Kim Il-song is the most constructive 
programme which helps realise the reunification of Korea in a 
peaceful way. 
  The messages wish President Kim Il-song a long life in good 
health. 
  Meanwhile, letters to President Kim Il-song were adopted at 
the Guinean national seminar on his famous work "For the 
ultimate solution of the rural question under the banner of the 
socialist rural theses" and at friendly gatherings with Korean 
visitors in Katmandu, Nepal. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

