<F P=100> North Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   Society to Promote Austrian-DPRK Ties Meets </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Society to Promote Austrian-DPRK Ties Meets </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   SK1505090094 Pyongyang KCNA in English 0819 GMT 15 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK1505090094 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, May 15 (KCNA) -- A general meeting of the 
Wiener-Neustadt branch of the society for the promotion of the 
relations between Austria and the Democratic People's Republic 
of Korea was held on May 5. 
  At the meeting the chairman of the branch reviewed the 
achievements and experience the branch has made in its 
activities over the past 15 years. 
  Referring to the vicious anti-DPRK campaign launched by the 
United States and its followers with a row over nuclear 
suspicion to stifle the DPRK, a socialist state, he said they 
always stand on the side of the Korean people. 
  "We will fully support the Korean people in the just 
struggle 
for national reunification and strive to further expand and 
develop the many-sided friendly and cooperative relations 
between the peoples of Austria and Korea," he declared. 

</TEXT>

