<F P=100> North Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   Burundi Parliament Supports DPRK Position </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Burundi Parliament Supports DPRK Position </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   SK1605051494 Pyongyang KCNA in English 0423 GMT 16 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK1605051494 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, May 16 (KCNA) -- The Burundian parliament 
expressed support to the memorandum of the DPRK Foreign Ministry 
dated April 20 which threw light on the main obstacle to the 
solution of the nuclear issue and truth behind it. 
  In its note to the DPRK Embassy in Burundi, it said that the 
threat to and pressure on an independent state by big powers are 
a crude violation of international law and a big obstacle to 
peace and security of the Korean peninsula and the world. It 
expressed solidarity and support to the stand and efforts of the 
DPRK to resolve the nuclear problem through its peaceful 
negotiation with the United States. 
  It called upon international organisations not to cling to a 
double-standard policy, blindly following the big powers, but 
act according to their ideas and reaffirmed undisputed support 
to the Korean people's struggle for the independent and peaceful 
reunification of the country. 

</TEXT>

