<H3> <TI>   Congolese Party Makes Appeal on Korean Situation </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Congolese Party Makes Appeal on Korean Situation </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   SK1605051094 Pyongyang KCNA in English 0420 GMT 16 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK1605051094 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, May 16 (KCNA) -- The Political Bureau of 
the Congolese Socialist Party on May 5 published an appeal on 
the grave situation created in the Korean peninsula. 
  Recalling that the United States has turned South Korea into 
a nuclear depot filled with mass destruction weapons including 
more than 1,000 nuclear weapons, grossly violating the Korean 
Armistice Agreement, the appeal said: 
  "The DPRK's proposal for negotiation to replace the nominal 
Armistice Agreement by a peace agreement and establish a new 
peace- keeping arrangement is a most fair measure for removing 
the hostile relations between the DPRK and the United States and 
realising negotiation." 
  Expressing the hope that DPRK-USA negotiation would be 
realized in a short time and measures be taken for bringing a 
lasting peace on the Korean peninsula where the situation has 
reached the brink of war, the appeal urged the U.S. Government 
to substantially contribute to world peace. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

