<F P=100> North Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   Turkish Friendship Delegation Praises DPRK </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Turkish Friendship Delegation Praises DPRK </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   SK1405215794 Pyongyang KCNA in English 1506 GMT 14 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK1405215794 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, May 14 (KCNA) -- The members of a 
delegation of the Turkish Association for friendship with the 
People of the Democratic People's Republic of Korea were 
interviewed during their stay here. They said though threat and 
pressure of outside forces against the DPRK have been 
intensified, the Korean people have registered tremendous 
achievements in socialist construction. 
  Member of parliament Ali Ibrahim Tutu said after visiting 
the 
construction site of the Rungna suspension bridge: 
  "I was deeply impressed by the sight of soldiers engaged in 
peaceful construction with safety helmets and welders, not 
military helmets and rifles. Though the mass media of the West 
are alleging that Korea is making war preparations on an 
extensive scale, they can never cover up the truth." 
  He said he was deeply moved by the strong spirit of the 
Korean people, who were doing their business with courage and 
composure even in a serious confrontation with the imperialists. 
  Mayor Gurbuz Capan of Esenyurt City, Istanbul, said after 
visiting the Mangyongdae school children's palace that he could 
see the happiness and the bright future of the Korean people 
through the beaming faces of children. 
  Noting that the Korean people without worries about food and 
clothing are granted excellent benefits and conditions by the 
state in educating and bringing up children, he stressed that 
Korea is an earthly paradise, a country of the people. 
  Female lawyer Senal Sarihan said Korea that has successfully 
built socialism is the ideological support to her. 
  Pointing out that Korea is a model for the world people 
aspiring after a new life, she stressed that the press circles 
of the West captive to prejudice must regain reason and 
properly look at and represent the reality. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

