<F P=100> North Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   Kim Chong-il Sends Centennial Birthday Table </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Kim Chong-il Sends Centennial Birthday Table </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   SK1405110994 Pyongyang KCNA in English 1039 GMT 14 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK1405110994 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, May 14 (KCNA) -- The dear leader Comrade 
Kim Chong-il sent a centennial birthday table to Pak Yong-sun, 
an old woman residing in neighborhood unit No. 24 in 
Toksong-tong, Tokchon City, South Pyongan Province. 
  Born into a poor peasant's family in Kongju County, South 
Chungchong Province, she underwent all hardships as a nurse-maid 
at a landlord's home from early years and then a tenant farmer. 
  It was not until she was embraced in the bosom of the 
Democratic People's Republic of Korea after the country's 
liberation that she could enjoy a worthy life of humanity. She 
actively participated in assisting the front in the period of 
the fatherland liberation war (1950-1953) and afterwards 
devotedly worked for the strengthening and development of the 
socialist motherland. 
  She is now the oldest woman in a big family of 50 members 
including her sons, daughters, grandsons and granddaughters. 
  All people in the DPRK are now living a happy life with no 
worry about food, clothing and housing, singing the prime of 
youth in the sixties and the first step into old age in the 
nineties, benefitting by the free health care system. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

