<F P=100> North Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   Kim Chong-il Responds to Letter Sent by Girl </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Kim Chong-il Responds to Letter Sent by Girl </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   SK1605051694 Pyongyang KCNA in English 0430 GMT 16 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK1605051694 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, May 16 (KCNA) -- The dear leader Comrade 
Kim Chong-il received a letter from Min Su-yong, a four-year-old 
girl of the Kuchon kindergarten, Sariwon city, the seat of North 
Hwanghae Province near Pyongyang, and sent the following 
autographic letter to her: 
  "I hope you will become a good student. 
  April 27, 1994 
  Kim Chong-il" 
  In her letter to Comrade Kim Chong-il Min Su-yong said: 
  "Dear leader, I have appeared on TV twice because I was good 
at composition, word contest and diary writing. 
  "My kindergartener felt very proud of this, saying if I 
appeared on TV, the dear leader would be pleased to see me. 
  "So, I have dreamed of being received by you. And I am going 
to keep diaries in a fair handwriting in the hope of having them 
read by you." 
  Min Su-yong is very inquisitive and has a good memory. She 
began to read books and learn composition from the age of 3. 
  In compliance with the party's intention to systematically 
educate children with rare aptitude and talent, the Kuchon 
kindergarten taught the three-year-old girl how to read and 
write the mother tongue in various forms and ways. It also 
taught the girl with keen observation and imagination how to 
properly see and judge things. 
  With her composition capacity increasing gradually, she was 
able to write to Yi In-mo, the incarnation of the faith and 
will, and to soldiers of the People's Army and kept diaries 
fairly, deeply impressing people. 
  Upon receiving the autographic letter of Comrade Kim 
Chong-il, Min Su-yong vowed to study hard with brothers and 
sisters and become a good little writer. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

