<H3> <TI>   KCNA Reports on Chemical Fertilizer Production </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    KCNA Reports on Chemical Fertilizer Production </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   SK1405050094 Pyongyang KCNA in English 0417 GMT 14 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK1405050094 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, May 14 (KCNA) -- Large quantities of 
fertilizers are now being produced by factories under the 
Ministry of Chemical Industry in Korea. 
  According to data available, fertilizer output jumped 20 
percent in the first ten days of this month over the 
corresponding period last month, taking the ministry as a whole. 
  The Namhung Youth Chemical Complex increased fertilizer 
output 68 percent in this period above the same period last 
month by putting all the equipment in full-capacity operation. 
  The Hungnam Fertilizer Complex is now turning out a large 
quantity of effective fertilizers suitable to the conditions of 
soil and the biological characteristics of crops. 

</TEXT>

