<H3> <TI>   Reportage on SRV Prime Minister's Visit Continues </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Reportage on SRV Prime Minister's Visit Continues </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Agreements on Bilateral Trade Signed </H4>

<F P=102> BK1305152994 Rangoon Radio Burma in Burmese 1330 GMT 13 May 
94 </F>

<F P=103> BK1305152994 </F>
<F P=104>  Rangoon Radio Burma </F>
<F P=105>  Burmese </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] A ceremony for signing agreements between the 
Governments of the Union of Myanmar [Burma] and the Socialist 
Republic of Vietnam was held at 1715 today at Hall D of the 
Seinle Kantha Guest House. 
  U Myo Min, director general of the Directorate of Hotel and 
Tourism Industry and Mr. Do Quang Trung, chairman of the Vietnam 
State Tourism General Department signed the agreement on 
cooperation in tourism between the governments of the Union of 
Myanmar and the SRV and exchanged the signed documents. 
  U Aung Thaung, deputy trade minister and the SRV deputy 
minister of trade signed the agreement on trade between the 
governments of the Union of Myanmar and the SRV and exchanged 
the signed documents. 
  Foreign Minister U Ohn Gyaw and SRV Foreign Minister Nguyen 
Manh Cam signed the agreement to establish a joint commission on 
cooperation between the governments of the Union of Myanmar and 
the SRV and exchanged the signed documents. The signing 
ceremony ended after the two foreign ministers raised a toast to 
lasting bilateral friendship. 

</TEXT>

