<F P=100> Brunei, Malaysia &amp; Singapore </F>
<F P=101> Singapore </F>
<H3> <TI>   Statistics Show 9.9% Economic Growth Achieved </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Statistics Show 9.9% Economic Growth Achieved </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BK1505122294 Singapore Singapore Broadcasting Corporation in 
English 1100 GMT 15 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK1505122294 </F>
<F P=104>  Singapore Singapore Broadcasting Corporation </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The Singapore economy expanded by 9.9 percent last 
year compared with 6 percent in 1992. Financial and business 
services was the fastest growing sector, expanding by 13 
percent. The Department of Statistics also revealed that, 
compared to the past 10 years, prices of private property in 
1993 rose by a record 24 percent. 
  Prices of land and houses alone shot up 41 percent compared 
with 15 percent in 1992. 
  The department also found that more middle-aged people are 
in 
the labor force compared with 10 years ago and a proportion of 
the elderly aged 60 years and above was also greater compared 
with 10 years ago. The number of elderly also increased at a 
faster rate than the general population. 

</TEXT>

