<H3> <TI>   EPA Chief Says Economy To Recover in Fiscal `94 </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    EPA Chief Says Economy To Recover in Fiscal `94 </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW1605125194 Tokyo KYODO in English 0744 GMT 16 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW1605125194 </F>
<F P=104>  Tokyo KYODO </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Tokyo, May 16 KYODO -- Japan's chief economic 
planner said Monday [May 16] the nation's economy will stage a 
bona-fide recovery during the current fiscal year. 
  "The Japanese economy will likely get onto a path of 
full-fledged recovery during fiscal 1994," which started on 
April 1, said Yoshio Terasawa, director general of the Economic 
Planning Agency [EPA]. 
  The economy will receive a boost from brisk housing 
investments and income tax cuts, which will help reduce 
inventories of durable goods, he said. 
  He predicted consumer spending will pick up, thereby 
improving private-sector sentiment, and that capital investments 
will eventually start recovering. 
  Consumer spending and corporate capital investments are two 
main driving forces for the economy. 

</TEXT>

