<F P=103> OW1605132694 </F>
<F P=104>  Tokyo KYODO </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Tokyo, May 16 KYODO -- Major Japanese electronics 
firm Hitachi Ltd. said Monday [16 May] it will establish an 
electronic device design subsidiary in britain next month to 
bolster its operations overseas. 
  The Tokyo-based company said the new firm, Hitachi Micro 
Systems Europe Ltd., will engage in designing computer chips and 
support tools as well as development of application technologies. 
  The company said the new undertaking followed a capital 
increase of 1.5 million dollars in April by Hitachi Micro 
Systems Inc., its large-scale integrated circuit design unit 
established in California in 1978. 
  The company said it will continue to strengthen its design 
and development operations in the U.S. and Europe to meet the 
needs of local customers. 
  The company has been producing semiconductors at its German 
subsidiary established in 1980. 
  It said its production base in the U.S. will start 
manufacturing microcomputers this fall at a monthly volume of 
300,000 units. 

</TEXT>

