<F P=100> NORTHEAST ASIA </F>
<F P=101> Japan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Toshiba Develops Improved Rewritable Optical Disk </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Toshiba Develops Improved Rewritable Optical Disk </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW1605024594 Tokyo KYODO in English 0135 GMT 16 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW1605024594 </F>
<F P=104>  Tokyo KYODO </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Tokyo, May 16 KYODO -- Toshiba Corp. said Monday 
[16 May] it has developed an innovative high capacity 3.5-inch 
optical disk system that has a partial rewrite capability. 
  Data can be entered on the new optical disk using a modified 
phase-change process, allowing it to be either partially or 
totally deleted by overwriting, Toshiba said. 
  In phase-change optical disk drives, the reading and writing 
of data is achieved by converting the recording layer of the 
disk from an amorphous to a crystalline state and vice versa, 
using the heat emitted by a laser diode. 
  Toshiba said the system represents a dramatic improvement 
over conventional rewritable magneto-optical disk systems, in 
which stored data cannot be changed without first erasing the 
whole section on which amended data is to be entered. 
  The new optical disk will be suitable for application in a 
wide range of next-generation multimedia products that run on 
personal computers, Toshiba said. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

<DOC>
<DOCNO> FBIS4-53099 </DOCNO>
