<F P=100> Cambodia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Interior Minister Says Demonstration Cancelled </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Interior Minister Says Demonstration Cancelled </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BK1705015194 Phnom Penh National Radio of Cambodia Network 
in Cambodian 1300 GMT 16 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK1705015194 </F>
<F P=104>  Phnom Penh National Radio of Cambodia Network 
in Cambodian 1300 GMT 16 May 94 </F>

<F P=105> Cambodian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Message from Interior Minister Yu Hokkri -- recorded] </F>
  [Text] My respects to the two supreme patriarchs, all 
venerable monks, and my beloved compatriots: 
  I, Yu Hokkri, minister of the interior, would like to 
present 
the following announcement from the Interior Ministry: 
  In compliance with the message dated 15 May of His Majesty 
Norodom Sihanouk Varaman, revered king of the Kingdom of 
Cambodia, in which he appealed to all brothers, sisters, 
children, grandchildren, and great-grandchildren to not hold the 
demonstration on 16 and 17 May so as to avoid any incidents 
which might bring about adverse consequences that will further 
complicate the solution that we are seeking for our motherland 
through peaceful means in line with Lord Buddha's teachings, 
Venerable Monk (Vichea Ratanapannha Wilson) and (Sit Kosangsin), 
representatives of the Kampuchea Kraom Buddhist Association, and 
the Cambodian Youth Association have decided to cancel their 
planned demonstration. 
  At the same time, a group of people have distributed false 
letters calling on the public to join demonstrations or meetings 
on 17 May in the name of the two associations mentioned above. 
  Venerable Monk (Vichea Ratanapannha Wilson) and (Sit 
Kosangsin) have rejected any undertaking that run counter to the 
wish and desire of the revered his majesty the king, who is the 
father of national peace. 
  The Interior Ministry would like to stress also that until 
now, the ministry has not received any new requests for holding 
the demonstration. 
  It is with the goal of ensuring security and public order 
that I would like your venerable personages and the public to 
please be informed. 
  Thank you. 
  Issued in Phnom Penh on 16 May 1994 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

