<F P=100> Indonesia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Summit Meeting With New Zealand Held in Jakarta </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Summit Meeting With New Zealand Held in Jakarta </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Suharto, Bolger Discuss East Timor </H4>

<F P=102> BK1605163994 Jakarta Radio Republik Indonesia Network in 
Indonesian 1200 GMT 16 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK1605163994 </F>
<F P=104>  Jakarta Radio Republik Indonesia Network </F>
<F P=105>  Indonesian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpt] Indonesia and New Zealand have agreed that New 
Zealand deputies need to visit Indonesia. Minister and State 
Secretary Murdiono said this when he briefed reporters on the 
results of talks between President Suharto and Prime Minister 
Jim Bolger in Jakarta this morning. He said the two leaders 
agreed that such visits would be beneficial. The minister said 
Bolger did not bring a petition on East Timor from New Zealand 
deputies. The prime minister simply asked the president about 
East Timor. Suharto said the East Timor people had decided to 
be part of Indonesia. Any resistance to the East Timor people's 
strong wish to remain part of Indonesia will be categorized as 
an act to undermine national security. 
  According to Murdiono, the two leaders also touched on 
matters to be discussed by the Asia-Pacific Economic Cooperation 
[APEC] forum. [passage omitted on Mrs. Bolger's social 
acitivities in Jakarta] 

</TEXT>

