<F P=100> Philippines </F>
<H3> <TI>   * Possible Military Equipment From South Korea </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    * Possible Military Equipment From South Korea </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   94P30051 </F>
<F P=103> 94P30051 </F>
<F P=104></F>



<TEXT>
CSO 

    [Editorial Report] The 20 April Jakarta ANGKATAN BERSENJATA 
in Indonesian on page 5 reported that the Philippines is 
interested in purchasing excess F-5 fighter jets and ships from 
South Korea as part of its efforts to modernize its military 
equipment, according to Lt. Gen. Arturo Enrile, the 
newly-appointed military chief. South Korea sold 12 patrol 
boats the Philippines at a sharply-reduced price last year, and 
was considering selling F-5 jets as well. This sale, however, 
must be approved by the U.S., since Korea acquired the jets 
through the U.S. military assistance program. Enrile pointed 
out that the Philippines is relying on only two 1960-vintage F-5 
jets to guard its airspace. The problem became very apparent 
when U.S. forces withdrew from the country in 1992. 

</TEXT>

