<F P=100> Thailand </F>
<H3> <TI>   Tax Exemption Agreed With Saudi Arabia </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Tax Exemption Agreed With Saudi Arabia </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BK1505102594 Bangkok THE SUNDAY POST in English 15 May 94 p 2 </F>
<F P=103> BK1505102594 </F>
<F P=104>  Bangkok THE SUNDAY POST </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The air transport tax exemption agreement between 
Thailand and Saudi Arabia will foster relations and cooperation 
in tourism, trade, investment and exports between the two 
countries, Deputy Foreign Minister Surin Phitsuwan said 
yesterday. 
  The signing ceremony for the Agreement for Reciprocal 
Exemption of Taxes on the Activities of Air Transport 
Enterprises took place last Tuesday in Jeddah by Mr Surin and 
Saudi Deputy Minister of Finance and Economics Dr Abdulaziz al 
Nasrullah. 
  "According to the Revenue and Aviation departments, the 
agreement would help reduce people's travelling expenses by 10 
per cent and promote air transport and travel," Mr Surin said 
upon his return from Jeddah. 
  The deputy foreign minister left Bangkok on May 9 for Jeddah 
as chief of Thai pilgrims to Mecca for the annual Haj rites. He 
is scheduled to leave for Saudi Arabia again on Wednesday. 
  The agreement was the first between the governments of 
Thailand and Saudi Arabia in the last five years, he said. 

</TEXT>

