<F P=102>   BK1105130994 Melbourne Radio Australia in English 0500 GMT 
11 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK1105130994 </F>
<F P=104>  Melbourne Radio Australia </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Iraq is closing its embassy in Australia as part of 
a second round of closures of missions in middle-ranking 
countries. Financial reasons are being cited, according to 
Australian officials. 
  The first round of closures occurred six months ago. Iraq's 
missions in Australia, South Korea, Argentina, and Hungary are 
among the closures in this second round. 
  Australian officials say the Iraqi Government plans to 
maintain some properties in Australia, but it is yet to decide 
how it will be represented in Australia. Australia does not 
maintain a mission in Iraq, but it is represented via Amman in 
Jordan. 

</TEXT>

